font.div: Shen gong yi jiang 神工意匠 is a Chinese “four-character idiom” (chengyu 成语) used to title the work. This chengyu is an idiomatic expression used to describe the sublime beauty (exquisite conception and compositional structure) of a work of art (e.g. architectural buildings, paintings, etc.) shaped not only as a result of human capacities and labor, but also thanks to divine intervention.
This chengyu has taken inspiration from the last line of a poem composed by Zhao Puchu 赵朴初 (1907-2000) entitled Pingdeng Yuan 平等院 “Byōdō-in Temple”."@en
